@{FG Shine}Welcome to AmiChannel News@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 14th issue of AmiChannel News.

I'm afraid that we have lost the last nine months for nothing. It seems that we
are in the same position than one year ago, just after the Cologne'98 show.

If you are connected to the Internet, probably you are aware of the news.
Otherwise, and to make a long history short, I can tell you that Jim Collas has
resigned as president of Amiga. Besides, Amiga left Bill McEwen, the PR guy.
The new president of Amiga is Thomas J. Schmidt, the former COO in Jim Collas
times.

Probably you are wondering why Jim Collas has left Amiga. Officialy, he has
resigned to pursue "personal interests". Unofficialy, something happend at
Amiga/Gateway. Or Gateway didn't like the Jim Collas plans or someone at Amiga
forced Jim to leave.

For whatever reason it was, Amiga has changed one more time its future plans.
The AmigaNG (aka Amiga Multimedia Convergence Computer) machine has been dumped
and there is not going to be a version of the Amiga Operating Environment for
computers. The new plan is to develop user interfaces which will be run under
other OSs.

What's that mean? Gateway is going to build the new set-top-box/game console
developed by Microsoft. So, the plan is to build something for the dreaded
Internet appliances under Windows CE. In short, Gateway has killed the Amiga.

The future of the Amiga community is uncertain. We are going to jump to another
ship, this is for sure, whatever computer it will be: PC, Mac, ... or AQUA.

Our last chance is under the community hands. Fleecy Moss and other Amiga
developers (Phase 5, ACT, Olaf Barthel, Carl Sansenrath, ...) has formed a new
consortium under the name of "Phoenix". The plan is to build a new platform, who
knows if it would be possible to use the Amiga name. I hope that this become
a reality because we know that the strong point of Fleecy projects is not that
they become true. Knock on wood.

I only know that I am missing Jim. He was the leadership/hero we needed and he
is not now with us. Jim, if you read this, thanks a lot for giving us a hope.
Sadly, Gateway has killed it.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

         http://www.saug.com/

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         http://www.teleline.es/personal/angelsau/

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         angel@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez Díaz - angel@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News.
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Mundo Amiga.
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
