@node not08 "OPERATION: COUNTERSTIKE CANCELLED - SIBERIAN SUN ANNOUNCED"

           OPERATION: COUNTERSTIKE CANCELLED - SIBERIAN SUN ANNOUNCED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

....surely not this soon! Yes, BlueBlack Solution will continue to work on
bringing you the best real-time strategy war game available for the Amiga. Enter
SIBERIAN SUN. This game has been in the works for a couple of months now but
kept under wraps until we where certain about Sadeness. Many of the routines
from Operation: Counterstrike have been replaced with new, faster, more
efficient ones. There are a host of new features which come as standard with
SIBERIAN SUN that won't/aren't available for any other RTS game on the Amiga.
Features such as:

   - AGA and CyberGraphX support in a range of screen sizes
   - Full screen, rendered cut-scenes for the beginning, success and failure of
     each mission
   - Sound Panning, Master Volume Control, Surround Sound (*)
   - Position Dependant Volume (PDV) Effects (*)
   - Optimised Routines for 040 and 060
   - Workbench Window Support
   - Various Weather Effects such as Snow, Rain and Fog
   - VERY Fast c2p routines for AGA machines, optimised for 040/060
   - Custom animation format supporting sounds for individual frames, these
     sounds incorporate surround sound and panning effects as featured in the
     game (*)

Features marked with an asterix require a full installation of AHI with the
relevent sound mode selected. It hasn't been decided yet but the game could be
made to support only AHI, either through a dedicated sound card or via good old
Paula.

Although the game will be playable on a 030 AGA machine (in low resolution only)
it's highly recommended that players have a graphics card and a 040/40 or
higher.

Look out for a presentation of the game to be featured on a future Amiga Format
CoverCD. Although the intro screens will have you believe it's Operation:
Counterstike, the graphics featured are actually from SIBERIAN SUN. There should
also be a CDDA track on the CD to go along with the presentation. Hope you enjoy
it.

More news should be available really soon, along with some more screenshots,
music and a demo.
