@node not21 "OPEN LETTER ABOUT POWERPC DEVELOPMENT"

                     OPEN LETTER ABOUT POWERPC DEVELOPMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In the last weeks there was a lot of confusion on the Amiga Market. We saw the
Phase 5 announcements concerning their G3 Board and Amirage. We saw the WOA with
the announcements from Amiga. And we are seeing the OS3.5 Development since
quite some time.

In the light of these confusing events it is time for clarifying our position
(see below who is "we"

We certainly hope Phase 5 will support WarpOS and Warp3D or will work with H&P
to allow WarpOS/Warp3D to support these upcoming G3 boards and Cybervision NG
cards. Our software relies heavily on Warp3D of which no PPC library version
exists or is even possible. We make extensive use of functionality only WarpOS
provides. Also our projects are in the meanwhile too much advanced to change
something this major like the used PowerPC Kernel, both out of commercial and
technical reasons.

Moreover, it should be remembered that WarpOS was endorsed by Amiga as the
official PPC kernel. In short: for economic and technical reasons we cannot
justify developing a ppc.library version of any of the below mentioned titles or
even future titles. Additionally it is very important for us that the WarpUP
Software will be available at the same time as the new hardware. The Amiga
cannot withstand another market split. We also hope that Phase 5 and H&P will
clear up the confusion with a joint announcement soon.

We:

   - Hyperion (Shogo, Heretic II, Worms: Armageddon, WarpFX)
   - Digital Images (Wipeout 2097 and other future projects)
   - The World Foundry (Explorer 2260, M&M, and other future projects)
   - Darkage Software (Supreme Effects Generator)
   - Colin Ward (WarpMAME)
   - Markus Poelman
   - Steffen Haeuser (WarpSNES, WarpHexen, WarpHeretic, FrodoPPC, Warped!)
   - Hellcoder
