                HYPERION BRINGS SMACKER VIDEO CODEC TO THE AMIGA
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Hyperion is pleased to announce that it has entered into a license agreement to
bring "Smacker", an industry standard video codec developed by RAD Game Tools
and used in over 1400 games, to the Amiga.

Smacker is currently available for Mac (68K and PPC), DOS, Windows 3.X, Windows
95 and Windows NT and provides for both file-format and API multi-platform
compatibility.

"We could have developed our own video codec", says Ben Hermans, managing
partner of Hyperion, "but since both Heretic 2 from Activision and Shogo: MAD
from Monolith use Smacker, we decided to cut down on development time for both
titles and license and port Smacker instead. On top of that, Smacker is really
very fast and very efficient if you are only using 256 colors. It is doubtful we
would have been able to achieve the same result with the limited development
time available to us."

Further information about Smacker can be found at www.smacker.com.
